{% extends "layouts/_base.njk" %}
{% set title = "Not.Bot | Reserved Names" %}
{% set menu = "products" %}
{% block content %}
    
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="hero reserved-names-hero">
        <div class="hero-container">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <h1>not.bot Reserved Names</h1>
            </div>
            
            <div class="hero-illustration">
                <img src="/img/name-tag.png" 
                     alt="Name tag line art illustration"
                     class="hero-image" />
            </div>

        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Four Benefits Section -->
    <section class="benefits-section">
        <div class="content-container">
            <div class="benefits-grid">
                <!-- Top Left Block -->
                <div class="benefit-block bg-white bg-pink">
                    <div class="benefit-image">
                        <img src="/img/globe.png" alt="Globe illustration" />
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="benefit-title text-pink">Use Everywhere</h3>
                    <p class="benefit-text">Use the same name across all sites. Never worry that someone already has your name when you join a new site.</p>
                </div>

                <!-- Top Right Block -->
                <div class="benefit-block bg-white bg-purple">
                    <div class="benefit-image">
                        <img src="/img/bird.png" alt="Bird illustration" />
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="benefit-title text-purple">You're Early</h3>
                    <p class="benefit-text">Reserve now! Get first choice of available names and secure your digital personality.</p>
                </div>

                <!-- Bottom Left Block -->
                <div class="benefit-block bg-white bg-orange">
                    <div class="benefit-image">
                        <img src="/img/infinity.png" alt="Infinity illustration" />
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="benefit-title text-orange">True Ownership</h3>
                    <p class="benefit-text">Own your chosen name forever. Reserved names don't expire and don't have to be renewed.</p>
                </div>

                <!-- Bottom Right Block -->
                <div class="benefit-block bg-white bg-teal">
                    <div class="benefit-image">
                        <img src="/img/exclamation-point_teal.png" alt="Exclamation point illustration" />
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="benefit-title text-teal">Brand Names</h3>
                    <p class="benefit-text">Reserve your professional name and variations before others claim them.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Below-the-fold Content Section -->
    <section class="content-section">
        <div class="content-container">
            
            <!-- Platypus and Explanation -->
            <div class="content-block platypus-block">
                <div class="content-image">
                    <img src="/img/platypus.png" alt="Platypus line art illustration" />
                </div>
                <div class="content-text">
                    <p>Imagine having the same username everywhere online. Instead of being @sarah2847 on one platform and @sarah_jones_NYC on another, you could be sarah.nb everywhere - x.com, LinkedIn, TikTok, and any future platforms that emerge.</p>
                    <p>To protect your privacy, <strong class="brand-notbot">not.bot</strong> gives you fun, anonymous names like 'supremely-amiable-platypus.' Reserved Names let you choose something more personal and claim it early!</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Julia Vanity Name System Block -->
            <div class="emphasis-block">
                <div class="emphasis-image">
                    <img src="/img/locked-name.png" alt="Locked name illustration" />
                </div>
                <div class="emphasis-content">
                    <h3 class="emphasis-heading">Julia Vanity Name System</h3>
                    <p>Think of reserved names as the "preview mode" for the upcoming Julia Vanity Name system. All of the reserved names will be pre-registered when that system launches. Pro subscribers get one reserved name, and Verified Creator subscribers get five. When the Julia Vanity Name system goes live, there will be no limit to the number of names you can buy.</p>
                    
                    <!-- Expandable section for autonomous system details -->
                    <div class="expandable-section">
                        <button class="expand-button" id="autonomousToggle">
                            How does the Julia Vanity Name system work?
                            <span class="expand-chevron">â–¼</span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="expandable-content" id="autonomousContent">
                            <p class="intro-text">The Julia Vanity Name system will be <strong>fully autonomous</strong> on the blockchain. The objectives of the Julia Vanity Name system are:</p>
                            <ul class="objectives-list">
                                <li>Anyone can register a name for an alias they own</li>
                                <li>No one can register a name for an alias they don't own</li>
                                <li>No one can prevent someone from registering a name</li>
                                <li>No one can forcibly take a name that has already been registered</li>
                                <li>Names do not expire</li>
                                <li>There will be a deposit required to register a name</li>
                                <li>The deposit for a name will be returned when the name is released</li>
                                <li>There will be a way to transfer or sell a name</li>
                                <li>The registry will not depend on ongoing maintenance from Julia Social</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- How They Work Section -->
            <div class="content-block">
                <div class="content-image">
                    <img src="/img/me_nb.png" alt="Name tag illustration" />
                </div>
                <div class="content-text">
                    <div class="signpost-item">
                        <h4 class="signpost-heading">Presentation:</h4>
                        <p><strong class="brand-notbot">not.bot</strong> Reserved Names and Julia Vanity Names will have a ".nb" suffix. For example, "myname.nb". Default petnames have no suffix.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="signpost-item">
                        <h4 class="signpost-heading">Verification:</h4>
                        <p>None. If you want the vanity name "Tohichi_Hikita.nb" even though your name is not Tohichi Hikita, go for it! Also, don't assume that someone's vanity name has anything to do with who they are.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="signpost-item">
                        <h4 class="signpost-heading">Time Delay:</h4>
                        <p>It may take up to 10 minutes after registration for your reserved name to start showing up everywhere.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Allowed Characters Section -->
            <div class="content-block content-block-reverse">
                <div class="content-text">
                    <h3 class="section-heading">Allowed Characters</h3>
                    <p>The reserved names system only allows the characters a-z, A-Z, 0-9, and underbar. The Julia Vanity Name system will have a larger set of available characters. Reserved names must be between 3 and 25 characters long. In considering whether a name has already been reserved, underbar is ignored, uppercase "I", lowercase "l" and digit "1" are considered the same, and uppercase "O" and digit "0" are considered the same. You cannot reserve names that could be confused for petnames.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="content-image">
                    <img src="/img/letter-a.png" alt="Letter A illustration" />
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section>
{% endblock %}

{% block scripts %}
<script>
        // Expandable section functionality
        const autonomousToggle = document.getElementById('autonomousToggle');
        const autonomousContent = document.getElementById('autonomousContent');
        const chevron = autonomousToggle.querySelector('.expand-chevron');

        autonomousToggle.addEventListener('click', function() {
            autonomousContent.classList.toggle('active');
            chevron.classList.toggle('rotated');
        });

        console.log('not.bot Reserved Names page loaded');
    </script>
{% endblock %}